          <div class="bio">
          <p class="bio">Alexandra is a second-year <a href="https://www.newschool.edu/nssr/phd-clinical-psychology/">Clinical Psychology</a> MA student pursuing a concentration in the <a href="https://www.newschool.edu/nssr/ma-concentration-mental-health-substance-abuse-counseling/">Substance Use and Mental Health</a> track. Her research focuses on attachment theory and non-verbal contingency between mothers and infants. Passionate about the parent-child relationship, she hopes to work clinically with children and their families in the future. Prior to starting at the <a href="https://www.newschool.edu/nssr/">New School for Social Research</a>, Alexandra spent 2 years as lab coordinator for <a href="https://www.beatricebeebe.com/lab">Dr. Beatrice Beebe's Mother-Infant Communication Lab</a> at <a href="https://www.nyspi.org/">The New York State Psychiatric Institute</a> and 1 year at the <a href="https://childmind.org/">Child Mind Institute</a> working clinically with children with selective-mutism.</p>
